race.description: Book In Mayhem In The Mounting Yard 21st Nov Hcp (C1)
race.comment: RESPITE (2) was backed off the map on debut (synthetic) and didn't have much luck. Went back and bolted in delivering her Maiden. She has plenty of scope for improvement and is likely to be just as effective on the turf. GEEGEES LEGACY (4) resumes and Darmanin's engagement suggests he's pleasing the stable. Missed a whisker here two back over this distance and has trialled positivly for his return. Maps well.  GEEGEESCHASER (10)  led and just missed on the synthetic and will be better for it. Back on turf no issue and she also has claims. THANKGODITSFRIDAY (1) is a former Kiwi resuming for the Keys yard. Shown ability and has the inside gate and 2kg claim. The late betting needs monitoring. Stablemate GOLDEN SWEET HEART (5) resumes and has shown enough to include at a price. Has a solid trial under the saddle and draws inside. Will carry just 53kg with the 4kg claimer engaged.
